IDCON, headquartered in the United States, announced the forthcoming publication of an autobiography from their founder. “This book has been 60 years in the making,” stated Christer Idhammar. “I’m detailing all the experiences that have led me to where I am today.” Christer Idhammar’s new book details his transformation from merchant mariner to reliability guru and company leader. Along the way, the reader will get tips on how to become a successful reliability and maintenance consultant and leader. “Christer is very hands on, nobody can break it down like him,” rhapsodised Brian Davies, former consultant and plant manager. The book’s release date is 16 September 2019.  Advance copies can be reserved via the IDCON website.